One way to solve an encrypted message if we know its language, it is to find a different plane text of a same language long enough to fill one sheet or so, and then be count the occurrence of each letter. We call the most frequent occurring letter the first second most occurring the second and so on. Then we look at the chiper text we want to solve and we also classify its symbols. We find the most occurring symbol and changing it to the form of first letter of plain text sample, the next common symbol is changed to the form of third and second letter and so on until we account for all symbols of the cryptogram we want solve 
